.*---------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP   NAME='GETDATE/ADDDAY'.Adds a Number of Days
:XH3.ADDDAY Adds a Number of Days
:P.Specifies the number of days to add to the current date. This could
be used to get tomorrows date.
:EHELP.
.*---------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP   NAME='GETDATE/SUBDAY'.Subtracts a Number of Days
:XH3.SUBDAY Subtracts a Number of Days
:P.Specifies the number of days to subtract from the current date. This could
be used to get yesterdays date.
:EHELP.
.*---------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP   NAME='GETDATE/ADDWRKDAY'.Adds a Number of Work Days
:XH3.ADDWRKDAY Adds a Number Work of Days
:P.Specifies the number of work days to add to the current date. This
works like ADDDAY but it skips weekends and holidays. For instance if
it is Friday and you add 1 work day it will return Mondays date.
:EHELP.
.*---------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP   NAME='GETDATE/SUBWRKDAY'.Subtracts a Number of Work Days
:XH3.SUBWRKDAY Subtracts a Number of Work Days
:P.Specifies the number of days to subtract from the current date. This
works like SUBDAY but it skips weekends and holidays. For instance if
it is Monday and you subtract 1 work day it will return the previous
Fridays date.
:EHELP.
.*---------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP   NAME='GETDATE/ADDMTH'.Adds a Number of Months
:XH3.ADDMTH Adds a Number of Months
:P.Specifies the number of months to add to the current date.
:EHELP.
.*---------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP   NAME='GETDATE/SUBMTH'.Subtracts a Number of Months
:XH3.SUBMTH Subtracts a Number of Month
:P.Specifies the number of months to subtract from the current date.
:EHELP.
.*---------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP   NAME='GETDATE/ADDYEAR'.Adds a Number of Years
:XH3.ADDYEAR Adds a Number of Years
:P.Specifies the number of years to add to the current date.
:EHELP.
.*---------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP   NAME='GETDATE/SUBYEAR'.Subtracts a Number of Years
:XH3.SUBYEAR Subtracts a Number of Years
:P.Specifies the number of years to subtract from the current date.
:EHELP.
.*---------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP   NAME='GETDATE/STRDATE'.Starting Date
:XH3.STRDATE Starting Date
:P.Specifies the date to start with. This defaults to the job
date, the system date or a passed date can be used as well.
:UL.
:LI.:HP2.*JOB - Default:EHP2. - The program will use the job date, any
date math preformed will start with this date.
:LI.:HP2.*SYS:EHP2. - The program will use the system date, any date math
preformed will start with this date.
:LI.:HP2.*PASS:EHP2. - The program will use a date passed to it. Use this
option to preform date math on any specific date. If this option is used
the INDATE parameter must be specified as well.
:EUL.
:EHELP.
.*---------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP   NAME='GETDATE/INDATE'.Input Date
:XH3.INDATE Input Date
:P.This parameter is only valid if the STRDATE parameter is set to
*PASS. This option allows a specific date to be passed in so that
formatting and date math can be performed on it.
:P.The date passed in must be character data in YYYYMMDD format.
:EHELP.
.*---------------------------------------------------------------------
:EPNLGRP.
